üìä TIER 1: DATA AUTHENTICITY ‚Äî Is this data real or fabricated?
üìä Benford's Law Analysis
üí° What this means...
Benford's Law says naturally occurring numbers (like financial transactions) follow a predictable pattern - '1' appears as the first digit about 30% of the time, '2' about 17%, and so on. When data doesn't follow this pattern, it often means the numbers were made up, manipulated, or generated incorrectly.
